by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that H. hispidusis sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F0723FF8CFCD5FE0468AC441C" baseAuthorityName="Elliot" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[806,931,509,542]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lanius">H. lanius</taxonomicName>
. Twelve subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
